{
  "texts": [
    "The orchestration of services and digital twins enables efficient and reliable network autonomy.",
    "High-level network autonomy enhances network adaptability and self-management capabilities, thereby reducing the need for human intervention as well as enhancing the stability and reliability of a network.",
    "It also enables faster adaptation of a network to evolving environments and demands, thereby improving network efficiency and performance and providing users with a better experience and service.",
    "The entire lifecycle of the 6G autonomous network comprises five key phases: network planning, deployment, maintenance, optimization, and operation.",
    "The proposed 6G autonomous RAN achieves comprehensive autonomous operation and management such as self-deployment and configuration, selfoptimization, self-healing, and self-evolution."
  ]
}